---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <main style="max-width: 700px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 2rem; background: #fff; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.2rem; color: #2d3748; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Getting Started</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #4a5568;">Welcome to the documentation! This page shows how to add new documentation pages to your Astro site.</p>
    <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #2b6cb0;">Steps</h2>
    <ol style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #374151; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
      <li>Create a new <code>.md</code> or <code>.astro</code> file in <code>src/pages/</code>.</li>
      <li>Add your content using Markdown or Astro components.</li>
      <li>Link to your new page from the navigation in <code>src/pages/index.astro</code>.</li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #38a169;">Happy documenting!</p>
  </main>
</Layout>
